This directory contains Mosquitto MQTT broker security configuration files.

The Mosquitto broker runs on the PHC gateway and handles the BLE-to-backend
sensor data pipeline. It receives ASCON-encrypted vital sign data from the
ASHA's Android phone (which acts as a BLE-to-MQTT bridge) and delivers it
to the backend for processing.

Expected files after deployment:
  - mosquitto.conf  — Main broker configuration (symlinked from infra/mosquitto/)
  - acl.conf        — Access Control List defining per-topic permissions
  - passwd          — Hashed password file for MQTT clients

Security configuration:
  - TLS 1.3 required for all connections
  - Client certificate authentication (mTLS) for gateway-to-cloud channels
  - Username/password authentication for local phone-to-gateway connections
  - ACL rules restrict each ASHA's phone to its own patient data topics

See infra/mosquitto/ for the canonical configuration templates.
